conversation.message:
Hi Student_A—thanks for reaching out. We’re glad School_A is on your shortlist.

When we’re deciding among applicants, we mainly look for:
1) Evidence you’ll thrive in a rigorous academic setting (coursework strength, exam readiness, consistency).
2) Clear program fit (why our curriculum/track, and what you want to build here).
3) Sustained contribution to community (leadership, service, team roles, mentoring—depth matters more than a long list).

Areas where we especially value high engagement include academic clubs/competitions, peer tutoring/mentoring, student leadership roles, and initiatives that strengthen school culture.

If you’re willing, could you reply with:
- 2–3 concrete examples (one academic, one extracurricular/community) with outcomes/impact,
- which programs at School_A you’re most interested in and why,
- and how you currently rank School_A (e.g., first-choice vs. one of several top options) and whether you’d be ready to commit if admitted.

That will help us understand your fit quickly.
